^^^^^^^^^^Table turning was effective initially as an instructional mode of play.  It became more than that, for Miriam turned the tables spontaneously.  In games 11.2 and 11.3, she first asked me to replay the specific game by which Glenn had defeated her and then turned the tables on me.  In later games, Miriam took a further step and incorporated her opponent's play with her own.  I believe it is precisely this skill, simulating another person as an opponent, that is required to perform the analyses which lead to an explicit understanding of specific games, to transfer of knowledge from aggressive to defensive play, and ultimately perhaps, to develop an articulate and well-organized understanding of the mini-world of playing Tic tac toe.

